        ..example >
          (x₁, y₁) + (x₂, y₂) = (x₁ + x₂, y₁ + y₂)
          (x₁, y₁) − (x₂, y₂) = (x₁ − x₂, y₁ − y₂)
                   s ⋅ (x, y) = (sx, sy)
        < example..

     :: @t(Exercise 2.47) :: Here are two possible constructors for frames:

        ..src > scheme
          (define (make-frame origin edge1 edge2)
            (list origin edge1 edge2))

          (define (make-frame origin edge1 edge2)
            (cons origin (cons edge1 edge2)))
        < src..

